result.execSummary:
The defendant Joshua Raymond Jashinski was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Battery [Modifiers: Domestic Abuse], a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 940.19(1).
  • Disorderly Conduct [Modifiers: Domestic Abuse], a class B misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 947.01(1).
  • Operate Firearm While Intoxicated, a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 941.20(1)(b).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

Joshua Jashinski appeared in custody in court with Attorney Jeffery Purnell. Matthew Puthukulam appeared for the State of Wisconsin.
Sentencing Proceeded. Statements by parties and defendant. Received & Filed, papers as to sentencing.
AS TO COUNT 3
The court sentenced the defendant to 250 DAYS in the House of Correction, consecutive, FORTHWITH, with credit for 68 DAYS time served, with Huber privileges for work within Wisconsin as approved by HOC, and AODA treatment. Court Waived all NON-Mandatory court costs, fees, and surcharges. Defendant to pay all Mandatory court costs, fees, and surcharges during probation period on Counts 1 & 2, any bail on deposit to apply, failure to pay results in a civil judgment. Defendant advised any violations will result in loss of Huber release privileges.

AS TO COUNT 1
The court sentenced the defendant to 8 MONTHS in the House of Correction, consecutive, straight time. Court STAYED sentence and placed defendant on PROBATION for 24 MONTHS, consecutive to Count 3 on this case, and Count 2 on 14CF1781.

AS TO COUNT 2
The court sentenced the defendant to 2 MONTHS in the House of Correction, consecutive, straight time. Court STAYED sentence and placed defendant on PROBATION for 24 MONTHS, consecutive to Count 3 on this case, and Count 2 on 14CF1781.
